events.description: Portuguese navigator Pedro Álvares Cabral lands in Brazil (discovery of Brazil).
events.html: • 1500 – Portuguese navigator Pedro Álvares Cabral lands in Brazil (discovery of Brazil).

events.description: Spanish conquistador Hernán Cortés establishes a settlement at Veracruz, Mexico.
events.html: • 1519 – Spanish conquistador Hernán Cortés establishes a settlement at Veracruz, Mexico.

events.description: Treaty of Zaragoza divides the eastern hemisphere between Spain and Portugal along a line 297.5 leagues (1,250 kilometres (780 mi)) east of the Moluccas.
events.html: • 1529 – Treaty of Zaragoza divides the eastern hemisphere between Spain and Portugal along a line 297.5 leagues (1,250 kilometres (780 mi)) east of the Moluccas.[1]

events.description: The second day of the Battle of Eckmühl: The Austrian army is defeated by the First French Empire army led by Napoleon and driven over the Danube in Regensburg.
events.html: • 1809 – The second day of the Battle of Eckmühl: The Austrian army is defeated by the First French Empire army led by Napoleon and driven over the Danube in Regensburg.

events.description: Texas Revolution: A day after the Battle of San Jacinto, forces under Texas General Sam Houston identify Mexican General Antonio López de Santa Anna among the captives of the battle when some of his fellow soldiers mistakenly give away his identity.
events.html: • 1836 – Texas Revolution: A day after the Battle of San Jacinto, forces under Texas General Sam Houston identify Mexican General Antonio López de Santa Anna among the captives of the battle when some of his fellow soldiers mistakenly give away his identity.[2]

events.description: The U.S. Congress passes the Coinage Act of 1864 that permitted the inscription In God We Trust be placed on all coins minted as United States currency.
events.html: • 1864 – The U.S. Congress passes the Coinage Act of 1864 that permitted the inscription In God We Trust be placed on all coins minted as United States currency.[3]

events.description: The first National League baseball game is played at the Jefferson Street Grounds in Philadelphia.
events.html: • 1876 – The first National League baseball game is played at the Jefferson Street Grounds in Philadelphia.

events.description: At noon, thousands rush to claim land in the Land Rush of 1889. Within hours the cities of Oklahoma City and Guthrie are formed with populations of at least 10,000.
events.html: • 1889 – At noon, thousands rush to claim land in the Land Rush of 1889. Within hours the cities of Oklahoma City and Guthrie are formed with populations of at least 10,000.

events.description: Spanish–American War: President William McKinley calls for 125,000 volunteers to join the National Guard and fight in Cuba, while Congress more than doubles regular Army forces to 65,000.
events.html: • 1898 – Spanish–American War: President William McKinley calls for 125,000 volunteers to join the National Guard and fight in Cuba, while Congress more than doubles regular Army forces to 65,000.[4]

events.description: The 1906 Intercalated Games open in Athens.
events.html: • 1906 – The 1906 Intercalated Games open in Athens.[5]

events.description: World War I: The use of poison gas in World War I escalates when chlorine gas is released as a chemical weapon in the Second Battle of Ypres.
events.html: • 1915 – World War I: The use of poison gas in World War I escalates when chlorine gas is released as a chemical weapon in the Second Battle of Ypres.

entities.name: Poison gas in World War I

events.description: The United Kingdom, Japan and the United States sign the London Naval Treaty regulating submarine warfare and limiting shipbuilding.
events.html: • 1930 – The United Kingdom, Japan and the United States sign the London Naval Treaty regulating submarine warfare and limiting shipbuilding.

events.description: The 1st Air Commando Group using Sikorsky R-4 helicopters stage the first use of helicopters in combat with combat search and rescue operations in the China Burma India Theater.
events.html: • 1944 – The 1st Air Commando Group using Sikorsky R-4 helicopters stage the first use of helicopters in combat with combat search and rescue operations in the China Burma India Theater.

events.description: World War II: Operation Persecution is initiated: Allied forces land in the Hollandia (currently known as Jayapura) area of New Guinea.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: Operation Persecution is initiated: Allied forces land in the Hollandia (currently known as Jayapura) area of New Guinea.

events.description: World War II: In Greenland, the Allied Sledge Patrol attack the German Bassgeiger weather station.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: In Greenland, the Allied Sledge Patrol attack the German Bassgeiger weather station.[6]

events.description: World War II: Prisoners at the Jasenovac concentration camp revolt. Five hundred twenty are killed and around eighty escape.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Prisoners at the Jasenovac concentration camp revolt. Five hundred twenty are killed and around eighty escape.

events.description: World War II: Sachsenhausen concentration camp is liberated by soldiers of the Red Army and Polish First Army.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Sachsenhausen concentration camp is liberated by soldiers of the Red Army and Polish First Army.[7]

events.description: Arab–Israeli War: The port city of Haifa is captured by Jewish forces.
events.html: • 1948 – Arab–Israeli War: The port city of Haifa is captured by Jewish forces.

events.description: Korean War: The Chinese People's Volunteer Army begin assaulting positions defended by the Royal Australian Regiment and the Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry at the Battle of Kapyong.
events.html: • 1951 – Korean War: The Chinese People's Volunteer Army begin assaulting positions defended by the Royal Australian Regiment and the Princess Patricia's Canadian Light Infantry at the Battle of Kapyong.

events.description: Red Scare: Witnesses begin testifying and live television coverage of the Army–McCarthy hearings begins.
events.html: • 1954 – Red Scare: Witnesses begin testifying and live television coverage of the Army–McCarthy hearings begins.

events.description: British yachtsman Sir Robin Knox-Johnston wins the Sunday Times Golden Globe Race and completes the first solo non-stop circumnavigation of the world.
events.html: • 1969 – British yachtsman Sir Robin Knox-Johnston wins the Sunday Times Golden Globe Race and completes the first solo non-stop circumnavigation of the world.

events.description: The formation of the Communist Party of India (Marxist-Leninist) is announced at a mass rally in Calcutta.
events.html: • 1969 – The formation of the Communist Party of India (Marxist-Leninist) is announced at a mass rally in Calcutta.

events.description: The first Earth Day is celebrated.
events.html: • 1970 – The first Earth Day is celebrated.[8]

events.description: Pan Am Flight 812 crashes on approach to Ngurah Rai International Airport in Denpasar, Bali, Indonesia, killing all 107 people on board.
events.html: • 1974 – Pan Am Flight 812 crashes on approach to Ngurah Rai International Airport in Denpasar, Bali, Indonesia, killing all 107 people on board.[9]

events.description: Optical fiber is first used to carry live telephone traffic.
events.html: • 1977 – Optical fiber is first used to carry live telephone traffic.

events.description: A series of gas explosions rip through the streets in Guadalajara, Mexico, killing 206.
events.html: • 1992 – A series of gas explosions rip through the streets in Guadalajara, Mexico, killing 206.[10]

events.description: Eighteen-year-old Stephen Lawrence is murdered in a racially motivated attack while waiting for a bus in Well Hall, Eltham.
events.html: • 1993 – Eighteen-year-old Stephen Lawrence is murdered in a racially motivated attack while waiting for a bus in Well Hall, Eltham.[11]

events.description: Japan's Prime Minister Junichiro Koizumi apologizes for Japan's war record.
events.html: • 2005 – Japan's Prime Minister Junichiro Koizumi apologizes for Japan's war record.

entities.name: List of war apology statements issued by Japan

events.description: The Paris Agreement is signed, an agreement to help fight global warming.
events.html: • 2016 – The Paris Agreement is signed, an agreement to help fight global warming.

events.description: Four police officers are killed after being struck by a truck on the Eastern Freeway in Melbourne while speaking to a speeding driver, marking the largest loss of police lives in Victoria Police history.
events.html: • 2020 – Four police officers are killed after being struck by a truck on the Eastern Freeway in Melbourne while speaking to a speeding driver, marking the largest loss of police lives in Victoria Police history.[12]
